title: Tech
description: This is a randomly ordered feed of the most recent entries from Tech, skipping any feeds with errors.

items.title: Kaltura acquires eSelf, founded by creator of Snap’s AI, in $27M deal
items.description: Kaltura acquires AI avatar startup eSelf to integrate generative AI into enterprise video and learning tools.

items.title: AI PowerPoint-killer Gamma hits $2.1B valuation, $100M ARR, founder says
items.description: Gamma is growing quickly, and profitably, its co-founder CEO Grant Lee says.

items.title: Google brings Gemini to the Google TV Streamer
items.description: The tech giant says the change will enable users to use their voice more naturally to access content and more.

items.title: Lenskart recovers from tepid open to close first day slightly above IPO price
items.description: Lenskart's public listing stirred debate over the nearly $8 billion valuation set in its IPO.

items.title: Rad Power Bikes faces shutdown in January without new funding
items.description: The company is "still fighting to find ways to continue" according to an email viewed by TechCrunch.

items.title: Why a lot of people are getting hacked with government spyware
items.description: Government surveillance vendors want us to believe their spyware products are only used in limited and targeted operations against terrorists and seri...

items.title: Asus ProArt P16 Review: The Fastest Windows Laptop
items.description: This just might be the fastest Windows laptops on the market. Don’t ask about the price.

items.title: 6Sense founder Amanda Kahlow raises $30 million for new human-replacement AI sales startup 1Mind
items.description: Amanda Kahlow has been quietly been back in sales and marketing tech for about a year with agentic startup 1Mind.

items.title: A better way of thinking about the AI bubble
items.description: AI isn't all or nothing, and even good bets can turn sour if you aren't careful about how you make them.

items.title: Scribe hits $1.3B valuation as it moves to show where AI will actually pay off
items.description: Scribe Optimize is the startup's next major offering to help organizations identify where AI will be most useful.
